post_text:
Parents,
Please keep this chart in mind when deciding if your child is well enough to attend school for the day. We understand that it is allergy season and there are MANY reasons your child might have these symptoms, however we are not able to guess what the reasons behind the symptoms are. PLEASE do not give Tylenol or ibuprofen and send your child to school. These medications can cover up symptoms and we need to be very careful, in the school setting, not to do that. If your student feels bad enough to need the medicine, they would need to stay home from school. Remember, we now have the Bearcat Care Center in which students can be seen for their healthcare needs. Thank you for your help in making sure we keep our kids as healthy as we can!
#bearcatsalltheway

Team Sports

The Charleston School District is excited to be moving forward with team sports. Tomorrow night is Senior High (8/18) and Thursday night is Jr High (8/20). We are asking that only family members attend the football scrimmages this week. This will keep our crowd smaller, and allow us to see if additional safety protocols are necessary as we prepare for our first home games.

The Department of Health has required the following guidelines be met:
‚Ä¢ Every other row of the bleachers must be unoccupied
‚Ä¢ 6-feet distancing between spectators and family groups (even if standing along fence)
‚Ä¢ Face coverings are required for all present over the age of 10, except when eating or drinking

#wearecharleston
~Melissa Moore

Josh Walker
August 16 at 8:38 PM ¬∑

PSA:
We have made the decision to go ahead and move our senior nights up for football and volleyball.

Senior night for football will be August 28th vs Dardanelle. On that night we also recognize golf, tennis, cross country, band, and cheer.

Senior night for volleyball will be August 31st vs Paris.

Our hopes are that we can have full seasons. In the event that we cannot, we will have at least been able to get this important event in for our seniors.

We are preparing for the worst, but hoping for the best.

Thanks for understanding. #bearcatsalltheway Feel free to share.

Booneville Elementary School Family
August 12 at 4:52 PM ¬∑

The Bearcat Care Center will be open daily starting August 24th. Upon completion of your enrollment packet to the Bearcat Care Center, students can be seen by Glenda King, NP on Mondays, Thursdays or Fridays from 8-11 by or Dr. Michael Miranda, MD on Tuesday and Wednesdays from 8-10 by appointment.

Mrs. Lucy Ray is our Bearcat Care Center Coordinator. She will take appointments and schedule with Mercy providers. Nurse Jessica Walker and Nurse Sarah Blankenship will also refer for appointments if they feel a student needs to be seen by a physician after contacting parents for confirmation.

Enrollment packets will be sent home with all students pk-12th grades the first week of school. The Bearcat Care Center is only open to the students of Booneville School District.

post_text: It's great to hear the Booneville Bearcat Band echoing around campus! #bearcatsalltheway
text: It's great to hear the Booneville Bearcat Band echoing around campus! #bearcatsalltheway

post_text: Well - there is an Article on the front page of the Booneville Democrat about the work Brian and I, with help from the Band Boosters and the Booneville School District Administration, have been doing to get ready for this year. We certainly don't consider that we have been doing anything extraordinary. And I am fully aware that all teachers, coaches, administrators are making all the preps they can for these unusual circumstances. But it is still very nice to get recognized and to get some positive PR for the band program. The article even mentions the date of our practices ! (Hopefully it'll help students remember to show up! ;-) ) We still don't have a 100% clear picture of what our band program's future will look like, but Brian and I are doing everything we can do as much as we can as safely as we can. If you are a Booneville person, please consider going and getting yourself a printed copy of the paper sometime today!

Josh Walker
August 4 at 3:38 PM ¬∑

Attention incoming 7th grade parents:

As all of you know, we‚Äôre having to make numerous modifications due to Covid-19. One of those is how we do orientation. We are giving two options this year.

Option 1: Follow this link to a virtual tour https://youtu.be/JbKyzUWyEzk

Option 2: In-person, scheduled small group tours.

Due to limitations, we are only doing in-person orientation for 7th grade students and students that are new to the district. Please reserve your spot by Friday August 7th at 11:00. We will have first come, first serve time slots for August 10th and August 11th. We will tour 10 students at a time and they will be required to wear a mask. Students will be given their schedule and shown around the building. Please call 1-855-675-3339 and press 3, then 0 to schedule an appointment. Our offices are open from 8-3 Monday through Thursday, closed for lunch from 12-1, and 8-11:00 on Friday. Thank you! #bearcatsalltheway

Due to limitations, we are only doing in-person orientation for 7th grade students and students that are new to the district. Please reserve your spot by Friday August 7th at 11:00. We will have first come, first serve time slots for August 10th and August 11th. We will tour 10 students at a time and they will be required to wear a mask. Students will be given their schedule and shown around the building. Please call 1-855-675-3339 and press 3, then 0 to schedule an appointment. Our offices are open from 8-3 Monday through Thursday, closed for lunch from 12-1, and 8-11:00 on Friday. Thank you! #bearcatsalltheway

His responsibilities will include tasks such as maintaining records, communicating up-to-date ADH directives, and working with with administration and staff to communicate with our community. 2020-2021 BES Kindergarten Students:
We are enrolling now! Come by the elementary office between 9-2 Monday-Thursday or 9-11 on Fridays to pick up a packet or register online using the link below.

Items needed to enroll in Kindergarten are:
Copy of birth certificate, social security card, current immunization record, current well-child physical for 2020, copy of insurance/medicaid card, and any legal documentation regarding custody if applicable.

You may scan documents or take a picture and send via email to christie.duggar@boonevilleschools.com.

May 7 at 2:01 PM ¬∑

UPDATE: Thank you for the overwhelming response! We are now currently booking for Friday, May 29th.
-------
With the closure of schools we have been unable to provide many of you with the Kindergarten/PK and Senior Cap and Gown photos we have provided for years.

Beginning Wednesday, May 13 we will be offering an in-studio cap and gown special by appointment only.

The cost will be $40 and will include:
2-8x10s
2-5x7s
16-Wallets
-------

MUST call or text 479-689-9727 to reserve your time slot. We are limiting traffic so to provide sufficient time for cleaning / disinfecting between sessions.

These photos will include your choice of the background pictured above or several other background options.

For safety reasons Seniors must bring their own Cap and Gowns. We have hundreds of clean K / PK cap and gowns available so are able to provide those without sharing.

Call or text 479-689-9727 to reserve your time slot.

Thank you!

May 1 at 7:29 PM ¬∑

Congratulations to both the 2018-19 and 2019-20 BHS yearbook staffs! The Arkansas Scholastic Press Association Conference was broadcast online for this year. The awards given are Honorable Mention, Excellent and Superior is the highest award.
The 2018-19 yearbook received a Superior rating (1st time we have received a Superior since T. brown has been adviser.)
The 2019-20 yearbook has received: Superior for Special Coverage, Emalie Miller for Pink Out. Honorable Mentions for Groups/Club Copy, Taylin Draper; Sports Copy, Emalie Miller; Student Life Layout, Shelby Posey; Academic Layout, Emalie Miller; People/Portrait Layout, Raven McCubbin; Groups/Club Layout, Kylie Rogers; Sports Layout, Raven McCubbin; Ad Layout, Staff; Student Life Copy, Raven McCubbin; Theme Development, Staff.
